 this detector to determine with high precision the\npolarization parameters (direction and fraction) for different irradiation\nconditions. Applying a judicious energy selection to our data set, we reach a\nremarkable sensitivity level characterized by an optimum Quality Factor of 0.78\nin the 200-300 keV range. We also evaluate the sensitivity of our device at 70\nkeV, where hard X-ray mirrors are already available; the measured Q factor is\n0.64 at 70 keV.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 5 May 2015 13:20:52 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-06"}
